 <bioghist encodinganalog="545" id="hb"><head altrender="history"><emph render="bold">Biographical Sketch</emph></head><p>Clyde Robert Bulla was born in 1914 on a farm near King City, MO. In his early years he attended a one room school house run by his older sister. He attended one year of high school before dropping out to help his family on the farm. He completed his education by correspondence. Although he wanted to be a writer, he was a farmer on his family farm until 1942. Then his father died and the family moved into town. He was a linotype operator and newspaper columnist until1947. From 1947 on he was a writer of children's books.

Biographical Source: Something About the Author, v. 139, pp. 45-49.</p></bioghist>
 <scopecontent encodinganalog="520" id="sc"><head><emph render="bold">Scope and Content</emph></head><p>The collection consists of production material for twenty titles, including typescripts, proofs, notes, articles and photographs.</p></scopecontent>
